snippet.textDisplay: Luv this big stylie ~ gurl, you are killing it!! 🤩😍 As far as dry lids are concerned, I actually use white cream makeup when they put out the Halloween makeup every year as a primer (I get it at Target for $1); I just put a dab on my fingers, apply to my lids, and leave it for about 10-20 seconds until it gets tacky, then put on my shadow 🙂 I use it all year round no matter what my skin is doing, and my shadow doesn't fade, smear, or crease, and it works with just about every palette (I've used it with NYX, Profussion, LA Colors, and  Colorworks in particular with great results) 😊
